00:00:04.297 --> 00:00:09.257
Namaste, I'm Lata Jain,
Welcome to Lata's Kitchen

00:00:09.257 --> 00:00:17.969
You can make various desserts with Carrot like gajar ka
halwa, gajar ki burfi, gajar ki kheer, gajar ka murabba

00:00:18.164 --> 00:00:21.257
Today I'm going to make Gajar ki Burfi

00:00:21.375 --> 00:00:25.945
Lets see the ingredients required
for making Gajar ki Burfi

00:00:26.258 --> 00:00:30.472
For this we'll need

00:00:30.742 --> 00:00:39.336
Carrot - 500gm, washed, peeled and grated

00:00:39.453 --> 00:00:42.116
Khoa - 250gm, grated

00:00:42.166 --> 00:00:44.330
Full Cream Milk - 500ml,

00:00:44.453 --> 00:00:47.259
Sugar - 150gm

00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:50.131
Almonds - 15, cut lengthwise

00:00:50.131 --> 00:00:52.171
Clarified Butter - 2 tbsp

00:00:52.336 --> 00:00:55.181
Cardamom Powder - 1/4 tsp

00:00:55.656 --> 00:00:58.917
Lets start making gajar ki burfi

00:00:59.155 --> 00:01:14.227
Take milk in a kadhai / wok, 
turn on the heat

00:01:17.477 --> 00:01:21.352
Add grated carrot

00:01:28.383 --> 00:01:30.685
Keep gas on medium high

00:01:36.375 --> 00:01:39.969
Keep stirring in meanwhile

00:01:40.984 --> 00:01:44.252
Cook till it gets dry

00:01:45.633 --> 00:01:48.732
Carrots have started getting softer

00:01:50.992 --> 00:01:52.953
Milk is getting reduced

00:02:05.219 --> 00:02:11.281
Keep stirring otherwise milk
may burn in the bottom of pan

00:02:16.594 --> 00:02:30.586
Milk is dried, now add the sugar

00:02:33.094 --> 00:02:42.258
Mix well

00:02:47.492 --> 00:02:53.904
It is again juicy, now we'll
cook it till it gets dry

00:02:55.734 --> 00:03:01.000
It is smelling like gajar ka halwa

00:03:01.938 --> 00:03:10.469
It has dried, now add
cardamom powder and mix

00:03:15.664 --> 00:03:23.883
Add clarified butter and mix well

00:03:25.297 --> 00:03:40.258
Juice has completely dried,
now add grated khoa to this

00:03:44.242 --> 00:03:48.264
Keep the gas low

00:03:55.680 --> 00:04:02.918
Now increase the heat, and cook it
till it gets thicker like a dough

00:04:10.445 --> 00:04:25.445
You can also add dry fruits to this
and have this as gajar ka halwa

00:04:27.242 --> 00:04:38.027
It is getting thicker and oil
has started to separate out

00:04:41.844 --> 00:04:45.401
Its consistency should be like this

00:04:48.359 --> 00:05:02.578
Take out the material in a greased
tray (greased with clarified butter)

00:05:13.383 --> 00:05:23.819
 Flatten it with a flat surface and
sprinkle copped almonds over it

00:05:26.594 --> 00:05:32.656
Press almonds a little

00:05:34.023 --> 00:05:44.590
Keep it aside for 2  hours and let it rest

00:05:46.727 --> 00:05:56.312
Its been 2 hours, now we'll cut it
into pieces of desired shape and size

00:06:08.469 --> 00:06:11.861
Take it out into a plate

00:06:16.594 --> 00:06:21.454
Gajar ki burfi is ready, it is very tasty

00:06:21.454 --> 00:06:25.992
You can serve it as a
dessert in lunch or dinner

00:06:25.992 --> 00:06:31.651
You can prepare this gajar ki
burfi for festivals or for guests

00:06:31.651 --> 00:06:36.052
You can refrigerate and eat it for 15 days

00:06:36.052 --> 00:06:39.391
Thanks for watching gajar ki burfi

